0 \le\int_a^b \left( f(x)-S_n(x) \right)^2dx \Rightarrow 0 \le \lim_{n\rightarrow \infty}\int_a^b \left( f(x)-S_n(x) \right)^2dx.
T_n =  \int_a^b \left( f(x)-S_n(x) \right)^2dx =\dots= \|f\|^2-\sum_{k=0}^n \gamma_k ^2 \|\varphi_k \|^2
f
f \in L^2([a,b])
(\varphi_k ) \subset L^2([a,b])
\gamma_k = \dfrac{\langle f \mid \varphi_k\rangle}{\|\varphi_k\|^2}
T_n
